<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-508-646  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 508 646.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  May 14 1990 v4 n19 p3(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bill could hamper smart-card use in benefit transfers, vendorssay. (portion of Farm Bill would limit electronic benefittransfers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Smart-card vendors are reacting strongly to a portion of thepending Farm Bill that reauthorizes the Department ofAgriculture's Food and Nutrition Service's (FNS) Food Stamp andTemporary Emergency Food Assistance programs.andP;  The particularportion causing concern restricts electronics benefits transfer toon-line systems.andP;  The timing of the proposal is particularlyawkward, coming as a contract is about to be awarded for a pilotproject to provide welfare benefits to some 6,000 to 10,000 peoplevia off-line smart cards.andP;  An FNS administrator notes that thelack of a mature off-line environment makes on-line technology themore logical first step for a technophobic government.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Smart CardsGovernment RegulationPilot ProjectsUnited States. Department of Agriculture.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>